Brazilian red meat production in1986 fell more than 20 pct to 1.9 mln tonnes due to droughtwhich reduced slaughter weight and to herd rebuilding whichstarted because of high cattle prices, the U.S. AgricultureDepartment said.    In its report on World Production and Trade Developments,USDA said that in 1987, beef production is expected to reach2.3 mln tonnes.    Pork production in 1986 rose 83 pct to 1.1 mln tonnes dueto the sharp rise in beef prices and is expected to remain atthat level this year, USDA said. Reuter&#3;